data.title: Queen's Road, Hong Kong
data.meta_description: View of Queens Road with Pedder Street Clock Tower being built (completed in 1863). This was the first road to be built in Hong Kong (1841-1843). Photographer possibly Milton M Miller (American) (1835-1899), his collection was transfered to S W Haley in 1863. 'Queens Road - Hong Kong' inscribed in album. Albumen print, 1860-1870 c.
